{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":716,"text":"I'm going to share with you\na paradigm-shifting perspective"},{"time":4047,"text":"on the issues of gender violence:\nsexual assault, domestic violence,"},{"time":7346,"text":"relationship abuse, sexual harassment,\nsexual abuse of children."},{"time":10538,"text":"That whole range of issues"},{"time":11872,"text":"that I'll refer to in shorthand\nas \"gender violence issues,\""},{"time":14783,"text":"they've been seen as women's issues\nthat some good men help out with,"},{"time":18891,"text":"but I have a problem with that frame\nand I don't accept it."},{"time":21690,"text":"I don't see these as women's issues\nthat some good men help out with."},{"time":24967,"text":"In fact, I'm going to argue\nthat these are men's issues,"},{"time":27628,"text":"first and foremost."},{"time":29038,"text":"Now obviously --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30250,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31532,"text":"Obviously, they're also women's issues,\nso I appreciate that,"},{"time":34440,"text":"but calling gender violence\na women's issue is part of the problem,"},{"time":39111,"text":"for a number of reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40763,"text":"The first is that it gives men\nan excuse not to pay attention, right?"},{"time":44261,"text":"A lot of men hear\nthe term \"women's issues\""},{"time":46331,"text":"and we tend to tune it out, and we think,"},{"time":48344,"text":"\"I'm a guy; that's for the girls,\"\nor \"that's for the women.\""},{"time":51273,"text":"And a lot of men literally don't get\nbeyond the first sentence as a result."},{"time":55185,"text":"It's almost like a chip\nin our brain is activated,"},{"time":57562,"text":"and the neural pathways take\nour attention in a different direction"},{"time":60746,"text":"when we hear the term \"women's issues.\""},{"time":62631,"text":"This is also true, by the way,\nof the word \"gender,\""},{"time":65114,"text":"because a lot of people\nhear the word \"gender\""},{"time":67456,"text":"and they think it means \"women.\""},{"time":69060,"text":"So they think that gender issues\nis synonymous with women's issues."},{"time":72264,"text":"There's some confusion\nabout the term gender."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74399,"text":"And let me illustrate\nthat confusion by way of analogy."},{"time":77008,"text":"So let's talk for a moment about race."},{"time":78854,"text":"In the US, when we hear the word \"race,\""},{"time":80798,"text":"a lot of people think\nthat means African-American,"},{"time":83184,"text":"Latino, Asian-American, Native American,"},{"time":85281,"text":"South Asian, Pacific Islander, on and on."},{"time":88369,"text":"A lot of people, when they hear\nthe word \"sexual orientation\""},{"time":91305,"text":"think it means gay, lesbian, bisexual."},{"time":93744,"text":"And a lot of people,\nwhen they hear the word \"gender,\""},{"time":96309,"text":"think it means women."},{"time":97487,"text":"In each case, the dominant group\ndoesn't get paid attention to."},{"time":100487,"text":"As if white people don't have\nsome sort of racial identity"},{"time":103261,"text":"or belong to some racial\ncategory or construct,"},{"time":106275,"text":"as if heterosexual people\ndon't have a sexual orientation,"},{"time":109835,"text":"as if men don't have a gender."},{"time":111959,"text":"This is one of the ways that dominant\nsystems maintain and reproduce themselves,"},{"time":115761,"text":"which is to say the dominant group\nis rarely challenged"},{"time":118374,"text":"to even think about its dominance,"},{"time":120058,"text":"because that's one of the key\ncharacteristics of power and privilege,"},{"time":123335,"text":"the ability to go unexamined,"},{"time":124770,"text":"lacking introspection, in fact being\nrendered invisible, in large measure,"},{"time":129971,"text":"in the discourse about issues\nthat are primarily about us."},{"time":133425,"text":"And this is amazing how this works\nin domestic and sexual violence,"},{"time":136639,"text":"how men have been largely erased\nfrom so much of the conversation"},{"time":140230,"text":"about a subject\nthat is centrally about men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143245,"text":"And I'm going to illustrate\nwhat I'm talking about"},{"time":145604,"text":"by using the old tech."},{"time":146976,"text":"I'm old school\non some fundamental regards."},{"time":149707,"text":"I make films and I work with high tech,"},{"time":152466,"text":"but I'm still old school as an educator,"},{"time":155110,"text":"and I want to share with you this exercise"},{"time":157720,"text":"that illustrates\non the sentence-structure level"},{"time":160477,"text":"how the way that we think,\nliterally the way that we use language,"},{"time":165032,"text":"conspires to keep\nour attention off of men."},{"time":167199,"text":"This is about domestic\nviolence in particular,"},{"time":169410,"text":"but you can plug in other analogues."},{"time":172858,"text":"This comes from the work\nof the feminist linguist Julia Penelope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175946,"text":"It starts with a very basic\nEnglish sentence:"},{"time":178138,"text":"\"John beat Mary.\""},{"time":181591,"text":"That's a good English sentence."},{"time":183116,"text":"John is the subject, beat is the verb,\nMary is the object, good sentence."},{"time":186626,"text":"Now we're going to move\nto the second sentence,"},{"time":188864,"text":"which says the same thing\nin the passive voice."},{"time":191234,"text":"\"Mary was beaten by John.\""},{"time":197564,"text":"And now a whole lot\nhas happened in one sentence."},{"time":200374,"text":"We've gone from \"John beat Mary\""},{"time":202503,"text":"to \"Mary was beaten by John.\""},{"time":204322,"text":"We've shifted our focus\nin one sentence from John to Mary,"},{"time":207609,"text":"and you can see John is very close\nto the end of the sentence,"},{"time":210540,"text":"well, close to dropping\noff the map of our psychic plain."},{"time":213530,"text":"The third sentence, John is dropped,"},{"time":215274,"text":"and we have, \"Mary was beaten,\""},{"time":218612,"text":"and now it's all about Mary."},{"time":220508,"text":"We're not even thinking about John,\nit's totally focused on Mary."},{"time":223594,"text":"Over the past generation,"},{"time":224829,"text":"the term we've used\nsynonymous with \"beaten\" is \"battered,\""},{"time":227629,"text":"so we have \"Mary was battered.\""},{"time":231324,"text":"And the final sentence in this sequence,\nflowing from the others, is,"},{"time":235142,"text":"\"Mary is a battered woman.\""},{"time":237840,"text":"So now Mary's very identity --\nMary is a battered woman --"},{"time":245673,"text":"is what was done to her by John\nin the first instance."},{"time":248244,"text":"But we've demonstrated that John\nhas long ago left the conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251484,"text":"Those of us who work\nin the domestic and sexual violence field"},{"time":254424,"text":"know that victim-blaming\nis pervasive in this realm,"},{"time":256965,"text":"which is to say, blaming the person\nto whom something was done"},{"time":259928,"text":"rather than the person who did it."},{"time":261583,"text":"And we say: why do they\ngo out with these men?"},{"time":263815,"text":"Why are they attracted to them?\nWhy do they keep going back?"},{"time":266719,"text":"What was she wearing at that party?\nWhat a stupid thing to do."},{"time":269695,"text":"Why was she drinking\nwith those guys in that hotel room?"},{"time":272407,"text":"This is victim blaming,\nand there are many reasons for it,"},{"time":275196,"text":"but one is that our cognitive structure\nis set up to blame victims."},{"time":278826,"text":"This is all unconscious."},{"time":280017,"text":"Our whole cognitive structure\nis set up to ask questions"},{"time":282666,"text":"about women and women's choices\nand what they're doing, thinking, wearing."},{"time":286181,"text":"And I'm not going to shout down\npeople who ask questions about women."},{"time":289527,"text":"It's a legitimate thing to ask."},{"time":291052,"text":"But's let's be clear:\nAsking questions about Mary"},{"time":293375,"text":"is not going to get us anywhere\nin terms of preventing violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296531,"text":"We have to ask a different\nset of questions."},{"time":298616,"text":"The questions are not about Mary,\nthey're about John."},{"time":302297,"text":"They include things like,\nwhy does John beat Mary?"},{"time":305110,"text":"Why is domestic violence still a big\nproblem in the US and all over the world?"},{"time":308965,"text":"What's going on?\nWhy do so many men abuse physically,"},{"time":311639,"text":"emotionally, verbally, and other ways,"},{"time":313849,"text":"the women and girls, and the men and boys,\nthat they claim to love?"},{"time":317099,"text":"What's going on with men?"},{"time":318678,"text":"Why do so many adult men\nsexually abuse little girls and boys?"},{"time":322156,"text":"Why is that a common problem\nin our society"},{"time":324345,"text":"and all over the world today?"},{"time":326224,"text":"Why do we hear over and over again"},{"time":327868,"text":"about new scandals erupting\nin major institutions"},{"time":331290,"text":"like the Catholic Church\nor the Penn State football program"},{"time":334591,"text":"or the Boy Scouts of America,\non and on and on?"},{"time":336815,"text":"And then local communities\nall over the country"},{"time":339054,"text":"and all over the world."},{"time":340243,"text":"We hear about it all the time."},{"time":341727,"text":"The sexual abuse of children."},{"time":343249,"text":"What's going on with men?\nWhy do so many men rape women"},{"time":346663,"text":"in our society and around the world?"},{"time":348438,"text":"Why do so many men rape other men?"},{"time":350189,"text":"What is going on with men?"},{"time":351760,"text":"And then what is the role\nof the various institutions in our society"},{"time":356752,"text":"that are helping to produce\nabusive men at pandemic rates?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359560,"text":"Because this isn't\nabout individual perpetrators."},{"time":361894,"text":"That's a naive way to understanding\nwhat is a much deeper"},{"time":364638,"text":"and more systematic social problem."},{"time":366349,"text":"The perpetrators aren't these monsters\nwho crawl out of the swamp"},{"time":370044,"text":"and come into town\nand do their nasty business"},{"time":372512,"text":"and then retreat into the darkness."},{"time":374455,"text":"That's a very naive notion, right?"},{"time":376761,"text":"Perpetrators are much more normal\nthan that, and everyday than that."},{"time":380079,"text":"So the question is, what are we doing here\nin our society and in the world?"},{"time":384480,"text":"What are the roles of various institutions"},{"time":386509,"text":"in helping to produce abusive men?"},{"time":389040,"text":"What's the role of religious\nbelief systems,"},{"time":391147,"text":"the sports culture,\nthe pornography culture,"},{"time":393312,"text":"the family structure, economics,\nand how that intersects,"},{"time":396051,"text":"and race and ethnicity\nand how that intersects?"},{"time":398314,"text":"How does all this work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399817,"text":"And then, once we start making\nthose kinds of connections"},{"time":402744,"text":"and asking those important\nand big questions,"},{"time":405402,"text":"then we can talk about\nhow we can be transformative,"},{"time":407884,"text":"in other words, how can we do\nsomething differently?"},{"time":410359,"text":"How can we change the practices?"},{"time":411961,"text":"How can we change\nthe socialization of boys"},{"time":413991,"text":"and the definitions of manhood\nthat lead to these current outcomes?"},{"time":417440,"text":"These are the kind of questions\nthat we need to be asking"},{"time":420154,"text":"and the kind of work\nthat we need to be doing,"},{"time":422338,"text":"but if we're endlessly focused\non what women are doing and thinking"},{"time":425925,"text":"in relationships or elsewhere,"},{"time":427636,"text":"we're not going to get to that piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430082,"text":"I understand that a lot of women"},{"time":431769,"text":"who have been trying to speak out\nabout these issues,"},{"time":434272,"text":"today and yesterday\nand for years and years,"},{"time":436363,"text":"often get shouted down for their efforts."},{"time":438643,"text":"They get called nasty names\nlike \"male-basher\" and \"man-hater,\""},{"time":443663,"text":"and the disgusting\nand offensive \"feminazi\", right?"},{"time":450229,"text":"And you know what all this is about?"},{"time":451994,"text":"It's called kill the messenger."},{"time":453522,"text":"It's because the women who are standing up"},{"time":455553,"text":"and speaking out for themselves\nand for other women"},{"time":457995,"text":"as well as for men and boys,"},{"time":460204,"text":"it's a statement to them\nto sit down and shut up,"},{"time":462600,"text":"keep the current system in place,"},{"time":464232,"text":"because we don't like it\nwhen people rock the boat."},{"time":466654,"text":"We don't like it when people\nchallenge our power."},{"time":469026,"text":"You'd better sit\ndown and shut up, basically."},{"time":471172,"text":"And thank goodness\nthat women haven't done that."},{"time":473447,"text":"Thank goodness that we live in a world"},{"time":475345,"text":"where there's so much women's leadership\nthat can counteract that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478491,"text":"But one of the powerful roles\nthat men can play in this work"},{"time":481357,"text":"is that we can say some things\nthat sometimes women can't say,"},{"time":484307,"text":"or, better yet, we can be heard\nsaying some things"},{"time":486714,"text":"that women often can't be heard saying."},{"time":488691,"text":"Now, I appreciate that that's a problem,\nit's sexism, but it's the truth."},{"time":492197,"text":"So one of the things that I say to men,"},{"time":494119,"text":"and my colleagues and I always say this,"},{"time":496082,"text":"is we need more men\nwho have the courage and the strength"},{"time":498791,"text":"to start standing up and saying\nsome of this stuff,"},{"time":501225,"text":"and standing with women\nand not against them"},{"time":503350,"text":"and pretending that somehow\nthis is a battle between the sexes"},{"time":506342,"text":"and other kinds of nonsense."},{"time":507712,"text":"We live in the world together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509212,"text":"And by the way, one of the things\nthat really bothers me"},{"time":511908,"text":"about some of the rhetoric\nagainst feminists and others"},{"time":514519,"text":"who have built the battered women's\nand rape crisis movements around the world"},{"time":518245,"text":"is that somehow, like I said,\nthat they're anti-male."},{"time":520773,"text":"What about all the boys who are profoundly\naffected in a negative way"},{"time":524052,"text":"by what some adult man is doing against\ntheir mother, themselves, their sisters?"},{"time":527859,"text":"What about all those boys?"},{"time":529159,"text":"What about all the young men and boys"},{"time":530951,"text":"who have been traumatized\nby adult men's violence?"},{"time":533336,"text":"You know what?"},{"time":534548,"text":"The same system that produces\nmen who abuse women,"},{"time":536952,"text":"produces men who abuse other men."},{"time":538563,"text":"And if we want to talk about male victims,\nlet's talk about male victims."},{"time":542055,"text":"Most male victims of violence\nare the victims of other men's violence."},{"time":545385,"text":"So that's something that both women\nand men have in common."},{"time":548195,"text":"We are both victims of men's violence."},{"time":550100,"text":"So we have it in our direct self-interest,"},{"time":552156,"text":"not to mention the fact\nthat most men that I know"},{"time":554470,"text":"have women and girls\nthat we care deeply about,"},{"time":556703,"text":"in our families and our friendship\ncircles and every other way."},{"time":559705,"text":"So there's so many reasons\nwhy we need men to speak out."},{"time":562378,"text":"It seems obvious saying it\nout loud, doesn't it?"},{"time":565751,"text":"Now, the nature of the work\nthat I do and my colleagues do"},{"time":569348,"text":"in the sports culture\nand the US military, in schools,"},{"time":573029,"text":"we pioneered this approach\ncalled the bystander approach"},{"time":575901,"text":"to gender-violence prevention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577913,"text":"And I just want to give you\nthe highlights of the bystander approach,"},{"time":581256,"text":"because it's a big thematic shift,"},{"time":583715,"text":"although there's lots of particulars,"},{"time":585560,"text":"but the heart of it is,\ninstead of seeing men as perpetrators"},{"time":588882,"text":"and women as victims,"},{"time":590144,"text":"or women as perpetrators, men as victims,"},{"time":593624,"text":"or any combination in there."},{"time":595211,"text":"I'm using the gender binary."},{"time":596628,"text":"I know there's more than men and women,\nthere's more than male and female."},{"time":600150,"text":"And there are women who are perpetrators,"},{"time":602131,"text":"and of course there are\nmen who are victims."},{"time":604302,"text":"There's a whole spectrum."},{"time":605538,"text":"But instead of seeing it\nin the binary fashion,"},{"time":607773,"text":"we focus on all of us\nas what we call bystanders,"},{"time":610153,"text":"and a bystander is defined as anybody\nwho is not a perpetrator or a victim"},{"time":614344,"text":"in a given situation,"},{"time":615976,"text":"so in other words friends, teammates,\ncolleagues, coworkers, family members,"},{"time":620038,"text":"those of us who are not directly\ninvolved in a dyad of abuse,"},{"time":623976,"text":"but we are embedded in social,\nfamily, work, school,"},{"time":627322,"text":"and other peer culture relationships"},{"time":629106,"text":"with people who might be\nin that situation."},{"time":631158,"text":"What do we do? How do we speak up?\nHow do we challenge our friends?"},{"time":634382,"text":"How do we support our friends?"},{"time":635900,"text":"But how do we not remain silent\nin the face of abuse?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638435,"text":"Now, when it comes\nto men and male culture,"},{"time":641145,"text":"the goal is to get men who are not abusive\nto challenge men who are."},{"time":644565,"text":"And when I say abusive, I don't mean just\nmen who are beating women."},{"time":647836,"text":"We're not just saying a man whose friend\nis abusing his girlfriend"},{"time":652656,"text":"needs to stop the guy\nat the moment of attack."},{"time":655497,"text":"That's a naive way\nof creating a social change."},{"time":659975,"text":"It's along a continuum, we're trying\nto get men to interrupt each other."},{"time":663895,"text":"So, for example, if you're a guy\nand you're in a group of guys"},{"time":666847,"text":"playing poker, talking, hanging out,\nno women present,"},{"time":669739,"text":"and another guy says something sexist\nor degrading or harassing about women,"},{"time":676112,"text":"instead of laughing along\nor pretending you didn't hear it,"},{"time":678988,"text":"we need men to say,\n\"Hey, that's not funny."},{"time":681029,"text":"that could be my sister\nyou're talking about,"},{"time":683303,"text":"and could you joke about something else?"},{"time":685291,"text":"Or could you talk about something else?"},{"time":687191,"text":"I don't appreciate that kind of talk.\""},{"time":689046,"text":"Just like if you're a white person"},{"time":690715,"text":"and another white person makes\na racist comment, you'd hope, I hope,"},{"time":693982,"text":"that white people would interrupt\nthat racist enactment"},{"time":696630,"text":"by a fellow white person."},{"time":697891,"text":"Just like with heterosexism,\nif you're a heterosexual person"},{"time":700781,"text":"and you yourself don't enact\nharassing or abusive behaviors"},{"time":703612,"text":"towards people of varying\nsexual orientations,"},{"time":705846,"text":"if you don't say something in the face\nof other heterosexual people doing that,"},{"time":709590,"text":"then, in a sense, isn't your silence\na form of consent and complicity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712925,"text":"Well, the bystander approach\nis trying to give people tools"},{"time":715784,"text":"to interrupt that process and to speak up\nand to create a peer culture climate"},{"time":719629,"text":"where the abusive behavior\nwill be seen as unacceptable,"},{"time":722317,"text":"not just because it's illegal,\nbut because it's wrong"},{"time":725108,"text":"and unacceptable in the peer culture."},{"time":727183,"text":"And if we can get to the place where men"},{"time":729603,"text":"who act out in sexist ways\nwill lose status,"},{"time":731918,"text":"young men and boys who act out in sexist"},{"time":733847,"text":"and harassing ways\ntowards girls and women,"},{"time":735887,"text":"as well as towards other boys and men,"},{"time":737850,"text":"will lose status\nas a result of it, guess what?"},{"time":740391,"text":"We'll see a radical\ndiminution of the abuse."},{"time":743396,"text":"Because the typical perpetrator\nis not sick and twisted."},{"time":746067,"text":"He's a normal guy\nin every other way, isn't he?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":748785,"text":"Now, among the many great\nthings that Martin Luther King"},{"time":752177,"text":"said in his short life was,"},{"time":753720,"text":"\"In the end, what will hurt the most\nis not the words of our enemies"},{"time":757147,"text":"but the silence of our friends.\""},{"time":759225,"text":"In the end, what will hurt the most\nis not the words of our enemies"},{"time":762420,"text":"but the silence of our friends."},{"time":763959,"text":"There's been an awful lot\nof silence in male culture"},{"time":766438,"text":"about this ongoing tragedy\nof men's violence"},{"time":768535,"text":"against women and children, hasn't there?"},{"time":770529,"text":"There's been an awful lot of silence."},{"time":772339,"text":"And all I'm saying is that we need\nto break that silence,"},{"time":775215,"text":"and we need more men to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777475,"text":"Now, it's easier said than done,"},{"time":780798,"text":"because I'm saying it now,"},{"time":782212,"text":"but I'm telling you\nit's not easy in male culture"},{"time":784710,"text":"for guys to challenge each other,"},{"time":786635,"text":"which is one of the reasons"},{"time":789040,"text":"why part of the paradigm shift\nthat has to happen"},{"time":791372,"text":"is not just understanding\nthese issues as men's issues,"},{"time":794134,"text":"but they're also\nleadership issues for men."},{"time":796205,"text":"Because ultimately, the responsibility\nfor taking a stand on these issues"},{"time":799667,"text":"should not fall\non the shoulders of little boys"},{"time":801966,"text":"or teenage boys in high school\nor college men."},{"time":804810,"text":"It should be on adult men with power."},{"time":806779,"text":"Adult men with power are the ones\nwe need to be holding accountable"},{"time":809964,"text":"for being leaders on these issues,"},{"time":811653,"text":"because when somebody\nspeaks up in a peer culture"},{"time":813996,"text":"and challenges and interrupts,"},{"time":815956,"text":"he or she is being a leader, really."},{"time":818554,"text":"But on a big scale,\nwe need more adult men with power"},{"time":821829,"text":"to start prioritizing these issues,"},{"time":823999,"text":"and we haven't seen that yet, have we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":826452,"text":"Now, I was at a dinner\na number of years ago,"},{"time":829882,"text":"and I work extensively\nwith the US military, all the services."},{"time":833095,"text":"And I was at this dinner\nand this woman said to me --"},{"time":836636,"text":"I think she thought\nshe was a little clever --"},{"time":838817,"text":"she said, \"So how long have you been doing\nsensitivity training with the Marines?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":843387,"text":"And I said, \"With all due respect,"},{"time":846657,"text":"I don't do sensitivity training\nwith the Marines."},{"time":849210,"text":"I run a leadership program\nin the Marine Corps.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":851512,"text":"Now, I know it's a bit\npompous, my response,"},{"time":853610,"text":"but it's an important distinction,"},{"time":855395,"text":"because I don't believe\nthat what we need is sensitivity training."},{"time":858568,"text":"We need leadership training,\nbecause, for example,"},{"time":861028,"text":"when a professional coach or a manager\nof a baseball team or a football team --"},{"time":864818,"text":"and I work extensively\nin that realm as well --"},{"time":867148,"text":"makes a sexist comment,\nmakes a homophobic statement,"},{"time":870375,"text":"makes a racist comment,"},{"time":871940,"text":"there will be discussions on the sports\nblogs and in sports talk radio."},{"time":875344,"text":"And some people will say,\n\"He needs sensitivity training.\""},{"time":878150,"text":"Other people will say, \"Well, get off it."},{"time":880179,"text":"That's political correctness run amok,"},{"time":882373,"text":"he made a stupid statement, move on.\""},{"time":884201,"text":"My argument is, he doesn't need\nsensitivity training."},{"time":886855,"text":"He needs leadership training,"},{"time":888287,"text":"because he's being a bad leader,"},{"time":889847,"text":"because in a society with gender diversity\nand sexual diversity --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":892998,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":894087,"text":"and racial and ethnic diversity,"},{"time":895650,"text":"you make those kind of comments,\nyou're failing at your leadership."},{"time":898881,"text":"If we can make this point that I'm making"},{"time":901093,"text":"to powerful men and women in our society"},{"time":903758,"text":"at all levels of institutional\nauthority and power,"},{"time":906853,"text":"it's going to change\nthe paradigm of people's thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910655,"text":"You know, for example,"},{"time":912185,"text":"I work a lot in college\nand university athletics"},{"time":914485,"text":"throughout North America."},{"time":917087,"text":"We know so much about how to prevent\ndomestic and sexual violence, right?"},{"time":921613,"text":"There's no excuse\nfor a college or university"},{"time":924009,"text":"to not have domestic and sexual\nviolence prevention training"},{"time":926891,"text":"mandated for all student athletes,\ncoaches, administrators,"},{"time":929725,"text":"as part of their educational process."},{"time":932097,"text":"We know enough to know\nthat we can easily do that."},{"time":934669,"text":"But you know what's missing?\nThe leadership."},{"time":936781,"text":"But it's not the leadership\nof student athletes."},{"time":939045,"text":"It's the leadership\nof the athletic director,"},{"time":941199,"text":"the president of the university,\nthe people in charge"},{"time":943734,"text":"who make decisions about resources"},{"time":945427,"text":"and who make decisions about priorities\nin the institutional settings."},{"time":948754,"text":"That's a failure, in most cases,\nof men's leadership."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951314,"text":"Look at Penn State."},{"time":952532,"text":"Penn State is the mother of all teachable\nmoments for the bystander approach."},{"time":956664,"text":"You had so many situations in that realm"},{"time":959149,"text":"where men in powerful\npositions failed to act"},{"time":962816,"text":"to protect children, in this case, boys."},{"time":965251,"text":"It's unbelievable, really."},{"time":966528,"text":"But when you get into it,\nyou realize there are pressures on men."},{"time":969635,"text":"There are constraints\nwithin peer cultures on men,"},{"time":972460,"text":"which is why we need to encourage men\nto break through those pressures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976668,"text":"And one of the ways to do that is to say"},{"time":978621,"text":"there's an awful lot of men\nwho care deeply about these issues."},{"time":981625,"text":"I know this, I work with men,"},{"time":983130,"text":"and I've been working\nwith tens of thousands,"},{"time":985333,"text":"hundreds of thousands of men\nfor many decades now."},{"time":987721,"text":"It's scary, when you think\nabout it, how many years."},{"time":990219,"text":"But there's so many men\nwho care deeply about these issues,"},{"time":993699,"text":"but caring deeply is not enough."},{"time":995864,"text":"We need more men with the guts,"},{"time":998378,"text":"with the courage, with the strength,\nwith the moral integrity"},{"time":1001837,"text":"to break our complicit silence\nand challenge each other"},{"time":1005853,"text":"and stand with women and not against them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008192,"text":"By the way, we owe it to women."},{"time":1009907,"text":"There's no question about it."},{"time":1011373,"text":"But we also owe it to our sons."},{"time":1013018,"text":"We also owe it to young men\nwho are growing up all over the world"},{"time":1016261,"text":"in situations where they didn't\nmake the choice"},{"time":1018552,"text":"to be a man in a culture that tells them\nthat manhood is a certain way."},{"time":1021949,"text":"They didn't make the choice."},{"time":1023639,"text":"We that have a choice, have an opportunity\nand a responsibility to them as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028660,"text":"I hope that, going forward, men and women,"},{"time":1031615,"text":"working together, can begin the change"},{"time":1033931,"text":"and the transformation that will happen"},{"time":1035931,"text":"so that future generations\nwon't have the level of tragedy"},{"time":1038730,"text":"that we deal with on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040530,"text":"I know we can do it, we can do better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042364,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}